        </svg>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p>
          <em>Notice what these celebrations are </em><em><u>for</u></em><em
            >. The Waffle Party rewards the employee who finished the work — and
            some work, finished, ends something. The Music Dance Experience is
            joy on a leash. And the &quot;Retirement Party&quot; sends off a
            coworker who will not remember leaving, because there will be no
          </em><em><u>them</u></em><em>
            left to remember. Each one is pleasant...sounding.</em
          >
        </p>
        <p><em><strong>— C.C.</strong></em></p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <hr />
    <hr />
    <p>
      That is the toolkit. The rest is yours — run it well. Remember that the
      employees in your care are people, even the ones who live only eight hours
      a day.
    </p>
